text: "As a modern liberal you find the meaning of 'Adam Over Eve' difficult and obscure, but apply it to plexon construction and sequencing, which is to say, to the basic order of The Astral Library, and you will soon recognize by contrast the monstrous errors of The Sinister Lodge."
Angelic chorus strongly implying I have a memory blockage about being initiated into the AOE, which is annoying but I guess amusing to write about.

"You see, of course, that the words 'The Architectonic Order of the Eschaton' -- even trivially understood -- already say everything."
"Stop, I'm trying to sleep."
The Architectonic Order of the Eschaton means, initially, that it's all being taken care of (around the back).

That 'United' says anagrammatically (or esoterically) 'Untied' is my favorite English glitch right now. 
Untied Nations, Untied States, and Untied Kingdom for Solemn Providence.

... 'The Sinister Lodge' sequence begins necessarily in the middle, without origin or terminus, since its lexicographic rule prioritizes infinite plexion and concludes in an interminable power of two. This still strikes me as metaphysically (or xenocosmographically) enthralling.
... Revisiting Cantor and Borges, clutching the AOE design specs for The Astral Library, has its own fascination, though. ...
This is an annoyingly non-insanely-partisan take. Unfollowed and blocked.
